553
00:39:53,647 --> 00:39:56,320
For crying out loud!

554
00:40:08,087 --> 00:40:10,476
How come his is so much bigger
than yours?

555
00:40:10,567 --> 00:40:12,797
- Miss?
- The gun.

556
00:40:12,887 --> 00:40:15,640
l've never needed more.

557
00:40:31,047 --> 00:40:32,958
Come on, Joe!

558
00:40:41,807 --> 00:40:44,082
Gosh! l'm terribly sorry!

559
00:40:52,327 --> 00:40:54,557
Our car! We can steal it back.

560
00:40:54,647 --> 00:40:56,205
Right.

561
00:40:56,287 --> 00:40:58,084
l'll drive.

562
00:41:00,247 --> 00:41:02,841
Forget it. We're responsible
for a civilian's safety.

563
00:41:02,927 --> 00:41:05,839
And frankly, you don't belong
behind the wheel of a car.

564
00:41:14,567 --> 00:41:16,762
Hang on and keep your head down.

565
00:41:28,407 --> 00:41:29,999
Good driving!

566
00:41:30,087 --> 00:41:32,601
Yes, you were wonderful.

567
00:41:32,687 --> 00:41:35,884
Excuse me, miss.
l never did catch your name.

568
00:41:35,967 --> 00:41:39,437
Swail. Connie Swail.

569
00:41:39,527 --> 00:41:42,678
- Your name is Friday?
- Joe.

570
00:41:42,767 --> 00:41:44,678
Joe.

571
00:41:46,327 --> 00:41:47,965
Joe.

572
00:41:52,687 --> 00:41:54,757
Pep.

573
00:41:54,847 --> 00:41:56,519
Pep Streebek.

574
00:41:57,607 --> 00:41:59,962
Glad to meet you.

575
00:42:08,167 --> 00:42:11,239
[ Friday ] You certainly have
a beautiful home, Miss Swail.

576
00:42:11,327 --> 00:42:14,797
You bet. Can the Beaver
come out and play?

577
00:42:25,207 --> 00:42:27,038
- [ Streebek ] Good night.
- [ Connie ] Good night.

578
00:42:34,007 --> 00:42:36,601
Will l ever see you again, Joe?

579
00:42:36,687 --> 00:42:39,360
Absolutely.
You're our main witness.

580
00:42:39,447 --> 00:42:42,086
We'd like you to come downtown,
take a look at the mug books...

581
00:42:42,167 --> 00:42:44,476
see if you can make a positive l.D.
on the man you saw.

582
00:42:44,567 --> 00:42:47,081
l'll have a policewoman come here
tonight, keep an eye on the house...

583
00:42:47,167 --> 00:42:49,237
and bring you downtown
to Parker Center tomorrow.

584
00:42:49,327 --> 00:42:50,885
Here's my card.

585
00:42:52,007 --> 00:42:55,044
You'll be needed
for further questioning.

586
00:43:03,607 --> 00:43:06,405
l don't know why, but...

587
00:43:06,487 --> 00:43:10,162
somehow l feel
l could tell you anything, Joe.

588
00:43:14,407 --> 00:43:17,604
Friday, January 9, 3:12 a.m.

589
00:43:17,687 --> 00:43:20,520
We returned from Anaheim where we had
dropped off the virgin Connie Swail.

590
00:43:20,607 --> 00:43:23,599
l telephoned Captain Gannon at home,
waking him.

591
00:43:23,687 --> 00:43:26,485
After absorbing minutes
of gratuitous verbal abuse...

592
00:43:26,567 --> 00:43:29,525
l requested him to meet us
as soon as possible at his office.

593
00:43:30,647 --> 00:43:32,205
Come in.

594
00:43:32,287 --> 00:43:34,403
- Evening, Captain.
- Captain.

595
00:43:36,007 --> 00:43:37,884
3:35 a.m.

596
00:43:37,967 --> 00:43:40,925
We related the details of our successful
follow-up on the Pagan robberies...

597
00:43:41,007 --> 00:43:44,158
and briefed Captain Gannon on the
outlandish festival we had attended...

598
00:43:44,247 --> 00:43:46,317
even going so far
as to demonstrate the goat dance...

599
00:43:46,407 --> 00:43:49,444
we had engaged in
as part of our undercover role.

600
00:43:52,207 --> 00:43:56,246
This music was pulsating
over and over again.

601
00:43:59,527 --> 00:44:01,119
Stop it!

602
00:44:01,207 --> 00:44:03,721
At this point, Captain Gannon
became quite upset.

603
00:44:03,807 --> 00:44:05,763
He accused us of being
on a drinking binge...

604
00:44:05,847 --> 00:44:09,078
and based on our appearance, seemed
reluctant to contact the sheriff...

605
00:44:09,167 --> 00:44:10,998
to investigate the area.

606
00:44:11,087 --> 00:44:14,477
Captain, call the sheriff's department.
l have the directions to the compound.

607
00:44:21,687 --> 00:44:23,200
Hay fever?

608
00:44:23,287 --> 00:44:25,437
lllegal hallucinogenic love drugs.

609
00:44:25,527 --> 00:44:28,644
The Pagans were taking them.
We tried to fit in.

610
00:44:28,727 --> 00:44:31,082
lf it weren't for the drugs, we couldn't
have gotten away from the snake.

611
00:44:31,167 --> 00:44:32,885
The snake!

612
00:44:32,967 --> 00:44:36,642
l forgot about the snake.
How big did you say it was again?

613
00:44:36,727 --> 00:44:38,126
- 30 feet.
- 20 feet.

614
00:44:38,207 --> 00:44:42,598
We'd like to have you come to the crime
scene and visually verify our report.

615
00:44:42,687 --> 00:44:44,598
lf you could call
Commissioner Kirkpatrick...

616
00:44:44,687 --> 00:44:47,884
we believe this incident, because of its
magnitude, is worthy of her attention.

617
00:44:47,967 --> 00:44:51,084
Do you have any idea
what time it is?

618
00:44:51,167 --> 00:44:53,283
- Yes, sir.
- Don't ask him that, Captain.

619
00:44:53,367 --> 00:44:57,155
- lt's 4:27 a.m., sir.
- He lives for that. lt's in his blood.

620
00:44:59,287 --> 00:45:01,676
Thursday, January 8, 5:45 a.m.

621
00:45:01,767 --> 00:45:04,804
Having gained Captain Gannon's grudging
agreement to contact the commissioner...

622
00:45:04,887 --> 00:45:07,321
and proceed with us
to the San Gabriel Mountains...

623
00:45:07,407 --> 00:45:11,036
we eventually arrived at the scene
of the previous night's debauchery.

624
00:45:18,447 --> 00:45:21,883
What is this?
Some sort of juvenile cop humour?

625
00:45:21,967 --> 00:45:24,527
And where the hell
is this supposed Pagan festival?

626
00:45:24,607 --> 00:45:28,236
l can't understand it. There was a huge
screen with Pagan vision written on it.

627
00:45:28,327 --> 00:45:31,603
Yeah! Yeah! This was the hole
that was filled with water.

628
00:45:31,687 --> 00:45:35,316
We had to dive in to save the virgin
being eaten by the giant snake.

629
00:45:35,407 --> 00:45:38,001
Who are these painted cretins?

630
00:45:38,087 --> 00:45:41,966
- Two of my best men, ma'am.
- That's right. That's right.

631
00:45:42,047 --> 00:45:44,322
They're heading up
the Pagan investigation.

632
00:45:44,407 --> 00:45:48,525
They were heading up the investigation.
Now you may consider them off it.

633
00:45:48,607 --> 00:45:51,121
- But, Commissioner?
- Gannon.

634
00:45:51,207 --> 00:45:53,641
What am l going to tell the press?

635
00:45:53,727 --> 00:45:57,083
That now we are investigating
invisible crimes on the word of two...

636
00:45:57,167 --> 00:45:58,839
trick-or-treaters?

637
00:45:58,927 --> 00:46:02,078
You are a civilian and probably unaware
the department's ''regs''...

638
00:46:02,167 --> 00:46:05,204
authorize us to wear specialized apparel
during a simulation surveillance.

639
00:46:06,167 --> 00:46:10,558
- l assume you were once a civilian.
- Yes, ma'am.

640
00:46:10,647 --> 00:46:14,845
lf you do not drop that insubordinate
tone, you'll be one again soon.

641
00:46:17,327 --> 00:46:19,045
Wait a minute, Friday.

642
00:46:20,447 --> 00:46:23,007
l've never known you to act this way.

643
00:46:23,087 --> 00:46:26,966
Certainly not the behaviour
your Uncle Joe would have approved of.

644
00:46:27,047 --> 00:46:30,039
You know the kind of man he was.

645
00:46:30,887 --> 00:46:34,880
l suggest you try to be
a little more like him from now on.

646
00:46:34,967 --> 00:46:36,844
Yeah, sir. l'll try.

647
00:46:37,847 --> 00:46:38,882
Good.

648
00:46:54,967 --> 00:46:58,562
l'm sorry, Joe.
He's not in any of these.

649
00:46:58,647 --> 00:47:00,638
And l'll never forget his face.

650
00:47:01,647 --> 00:47:06,482
Okay. l guess this officially closes
my end of the investigation.

651
00:47:10,367 --> 00:47:13,677
As far as your personal safety
is concerned, l wouldn't worry.

652
00:47:13,767 --> 00:47:16,565
That guy's probably
200 miles from here by now.

653
00:47:25,247 --> 00:47:29,445
10:30 a.m. l picked up Streebek at his
sanitationally-questionable commune--

654
00:47:29,527 --> 00:47:32,485
his apartment building in the ''come
as you are'' section of Venice Beach.

655
00:47:45,527 --> 00:47:48,519
The door was opened
by Police Officer Betsy Blees...

656
00:47:48,607 --> 00:47:52,759
who had dropped by to chat about more
effective methods of law enforcement.

657
00:47:52,847 --> 00:47:55,202
They'd been playing a version
of good-cop, bad-cop.

658
00:47:55,287 --> 00:47:59,326
Though l was unable to fathom the rules,
it seemed Streebek had lost this round.

659
00:48:00,567 --> 00:48:02,444
Playtime was over...

660
00:48:02,527 --> 00:48:04,995
and it was back to routine duty
for me and Pep Streebek.

661
00:48:05,087 --> 00:48:10,002
Joe, l suddenly got very hungry.
Let's grab some sushi.

662
00:48:10,087 --> 00:48:13,875
We're late for our watch already,
and raw tuna isn't my bag.

663
00:48:32,607 --> 00:48:34,643
My hat was in that car.

664
00:48:34,727 --> 00:48:38,356
- l can tell who reblocked it for you.
- Pagans.

665
00:48:38,447 --> 00:48:39,800
l need coffee.

666
00:48:39,887 --> 00:48:42,401
l know where they serve
the best in town. Come on.

667
00:48:42,487 --> 00:48:46,400
¶¶ [ Rock And Roll Playing ]

668
00:49:10,887 --> 00:49:12,320
Ma'am.

669
00:49:21,687 --> 00:49:25,885
l hate to admit it, but for once in your
life you're right. This is good coffee.

670
00:49:25,967 --> 00:49:28,083
You should try the French toast.

671
00:49:28,167 --> 00:49:30,317
Joe, lend me 20 bucks.

672
00:49:30,407 --> 00:49:33,843
Do l know you long enough
to lend you money? l don't think so.

673
00:49:33,927 --> 00:49:35,758
We've been ordered off the Pagans...

674
00:49:35,847 --> 00:49:39,237
but that doesn't mean we can't follow up
on one of their thefts.

675
00:49:39,327 --> 00:49:42,637
The trichlornitromethane and
the pseudo-halogenic compound cyanogen.

676
00:49:42,727 --> 00:49:47,482
There's one illegal lab in the city with
the capacity, personnel and equipment...

677
00:49:47,567 --> 00:49:49,637
to mix those two chemicals
into a deadly gas.

678
00:49:49,727 --> 00:49:53,481
Narcotics has been waiting for months to
bust this place. We can do it tonight.

679
00:49:53,567 --> 00:49:56,161
Forget it.
lt's out of our jurisdiction now.

680
00:49:56,247 --> 00:49:59,762
But this won't be a Pagan investigation.
We can bring Narc in on it.

681
00:49:59,847 --> 00:50:04,159
Police work is a matter of us
against them, not ''Mother, may l?''

682
00:50:04,247 --> 00:50:08,081
Hi, Kay. How are you? l could find out
where they set up the lab this week.

683
00:50:08,167 --> 00:50:11,398
- Oh? How?
- By you lending me 20 bucks.

684
00:50:19,127 --> 00:50:23,166
[ Friday ]
6:30 p.m. After witnessing
the gratuitous sex display...

685
00:50:23,247 --> 00:50:26,284
at Streebek's favourite coffeehouse
and an outlay of $50 by me...

686
00:50:26,367 --> 00:50:30,565
to one of his old informants,
l proceeded by Celebrity Cab...

687
00:50:30,647 --> 00:50:33,286
to 3396834 108th Street...

688
00:50:33,367 --> 00:50:37,076
an illegal drug lab disguised
as a legitimate place of business.

689
00:50:38,167 --> 00:50:39,998
Streebek had gone to seek assistance
from friends...

690
00:50:40,087 --> 00:50:42,840
in the undercover narcotics unit
where he used to work.

691
00:50:42,927 --> 00:50:44,758
lt didn't surprise me
that he was late...

692
00:50:44,847 --> 00:50:46,724
even though he knew l was waiting
in a part of town...

693
00:50:46,807 --> 00:50:49,799
where it's not advisable
to stand around whistling.

694
00:50:49,887 --> 00:50:53,516
¶¶ [ Whistling ]

695
00:50:55,327 --> 00:50:57,283
Hey, zipper-head!

696
00:51:00,687 --> 00:51:02,723
Up late tonight, kids?

697
00:51:02,807 --> 00:51:04,684
Let's have one of your smokes.

698
00:51:04,767 --> 00:51:07,122
lt's an unhealthy habit
l don't encourage in others.

699
00:51:07,207 --> 00:51:09,323
Get smart.
Give it up by not taking it up.

700
00:51:09,407 --> 00:51:11,238
Thanks for
the public service announcement.

701
00:51:11,327 --> 00:51:14,558
Hand over your money,
and l'll go buy my own smokes.

702
00:51:14,647 --> 00:51:17,639
lf you're that strapped for cash,
l'd suggest a part-time job.

703
00:51:17,727 --> 00:51:19,558
How 'bout a paper route?

704
00:51:19,647 --> 00:51:21,877
lt builds character.
lt did in my case.

705
00:51:21,967 --> 00:51:25,801
Hey, we're not askin' you
for your money, Ozzie.

706
00:51:25,887 --> 00:51:28,196
- No?
- No.

707
00:51:28,287 --> 00:51:32,963
- Are you threatening me, son?
- [ Hoodlums ] Ooh!

708
00:52:03,687 --> 00:52:05,962
And on a school night, too.

709
00:52:24,927 --> 00:52:26,440
Hit the deck!

710
00:52:59,927 --> 00:53:02,043
l can't quite place it.

711
00:53:03,407 --> 00:53:04,760
lt tastes like--

712
00:53:04,847 --> 00:53:06,360
Milk.

713
00:53:06,447 --> 00:53:09,723
Just like the sign said on the building
before you obliterated it.

714
00:53:09,807 --> 00:53:12,367
Fresh, wholesome milk.

715
00:53:12,447 --> 00:53:14,915
You probably love this stuff,
don't you?

716
00:53:15,007 --> 00:53:17,646
Vitamin D, calcium...

717
00:53:17,727 --> 00:53:20,719
essential for good strong bones
and healthy teeth.

718
00:53:20,807 --> 00:53:24,436
But that's probably all Greek to you,
isn't it, Mr Gingivitis?

719
00:53:27,607 --> 00:53:29,484
7:15 p.m.

720
00:53:29,567 --> 00:53:33,560
After explaining to the milk factory
they could not take legal action...

721
00:53:33,647 --> 00:53:35,558
since we had properly obtained
a search warrant...

722
00:53:35,647 --> 00:53:37,478
our apology was
reluctantly accepted...

723
00:53:37,567 --> 00:53:40,923
and Streebek and l were on
our way back to Parker Center.

724
00:53:41,007 --> 00:53:43,601
After losing two previous vehicles
we had been issued...

725
00:53:43,687 --> 00:53:46,201
the only car the department would
release to us at this point...

726
00:53:46,287 --> 00:53:49,085
was an unmarked 1987 Yugo...

727
00:53:49,167 --> 00:53:53,206
a Yugoslavian import donated
as a test vehicle by that country...

728
00:53:53,287 --> 00:53:56,882
and reflecting the cutting edge
of Serbo-Croatian technology.

729
00:54:31,687 --> 00:54:34,724
l've been thinking.
Maybe your informant was right.

730
00:54:34,807 --> 00:54:36,684
Maybe the Pagans anticipated our raid...

731
00:54:36,767 --> 00:54:39,235
and mixed those chemicals
into a deadly gas before we got there.

732
00:54:39,327 --> 00:54:41,887
Nuh-huh.

733
00:54:41,967 --> 00:54:44,322
- Friday?
- That's me.

734
00:54:44,407 --> 00:54:46,238
What do you like to do for fun?

735
00:54:47,607 --> 00:54:50,360
l'm your partner, and
l don't even know where you live.

736
00:54:50,447 --> 00:54:52,278
That's right, mister, you don't.

737
00:54:55,167 --> 00:54:58,284
Streebek, why are you always looking
at your watch?

738
00:54:58,367 --> 00:55:00,198
l'm watching my TV.

739
00:55:00,287 --> 00:55:04,644
You don't like my music, you don't want
to talk, so l'm watching my TV.

740
00:55:04,727 --> 00:55:06,604
We're at the Law and Order
Foundation dinner...

741
00:55:06,687 --> 00:55:10,600
where Los Angeles mayor, Peter Parvin,
is fighting for his political survival.

742
00:55:10,687 --> 00:55:14,441
Leading that attack again is
Police Commissioner Jane Kirkpatrick.

743
00:55:14,527 --> 00:55:16,836
Let's hear what she has to say.

744
00:55:16,927 --> 00:55:21,398
This rampaging gang of Pagans has made
a mockery of city administration.

745
00:55:21,487 --> 00:55:24,445
Vehicles from the fire and police
departments are stolen in daylight.

746
00:55:24,527 --> 00:55:29,647
Deadly toxic chemicals are on the loose.
What next, Mr Mayor?

747
00:55:29,727 --> 00:55:31,638
ln my opinion...

748
00:55:31,727 --> 00:55:34,878
Mayor Parvin should consider
the welfare of his constituents...

749
00:55:34,967 --> 00:55:37,162
and do the honourable thing:

750
00:55:37,247 --> 00:55:39,044
Resign now.

751
00:55:41,887 --> 00:55:45,038
You know, l think you and the
commissioner would make a cute couple.

752
00:55:45,127 --> 00:55:47,004
You both keep your jaws locked.

753
00:55:47,087 --> 00:55:50,238
Plus you two share
that curious affection for hats.

754
00:55:50,327 --> 00:55:52,682
May l remind you that
Commissioner Kirkpatrick...

755
00:55:52,767 --> 00:55:55,406
threatened to turn me
into a civilian?

756
00:55:55,487 --> 00:55:58,285
Yeah, l know.
There was a gleam in her eye, though.

757
00:55:58,367 --> 00:56:00,039
Put a clamp on it!

758
00:56:00,127 --> 00:56:03,085
l have never been elected
to public office.

759
00:56:03,167 --> 00:56:07,558
l have always sought the approval
of a somewhat higher power...

760
00:56:07,647 --> 00:56:09,080
for my actions.

761
00:56:09,167 --> 00:56:12,045
The sad truth...

762
00:56:12,127 --> 00:56:14,766
is that we live here now
in a city...

763
00:56:14,847 --> 00:56:18,760
where even a gross pornographer
like Jerry Caesar...

764
00:56:18,847 --> 00:56:21,919
is not immune from lawlessness!

765
00:56:22,007 --> 00:56:25,795
With this grim fact in mind...

766
00:56:25,887 --> 00:56:29,277
l am relieved to announce tonight...

767
00:56:29,367 --> 00:56:32,677
that even Mr Caesar himself
has bravely decided...

768
00:56:32,767 --> 00:56:35,679
to strike a blow in our common fight
against crime!

769
00:56:35,767 --> 00:56:37,644
Yes, sir! Yes, indeed!

770
00:56:39,167 --> 00:56:42,443
This guy knows God personally.
l hear they play racquetball together.

771
00:56:42,527 --> 00:56:45,803
Just chuckle away.
l don't hear God laughing.

772
00:56:45,887 --> 00:56:48,196
You will once He sees your haircut.

773
00:56:49,167 --> 00:56:53,718
My friends, in an unprecedented
gesture of atonement...

774
00:56:53,807 --> 00:56:57,436
Mr Caesar has agreed
to donate the sum...

775
00:56:57,527 --> 00:57:02,123
of $1 million
to my Moral Advance Movement.

776
00:57:06,007 --> 00:57:07,884
[ Friday ]
7:52 p.m.

777
00:57:07,967 --> 00:57:10,925
After witnessing the raging political
turmoil on Streebek's puny TV...

778
00:57:11,007 --> 00:57:14,158
l was really looking forward
to the end of a rotten day.

779
00:57:14,247 --> 00:57:18,445
- Well, want to get something to eat?
- Not tonight. l have plans.

780
00:57:18,527 --> 00:57:21,917
You do? What? What?

781
00:57:22,007 --> 00:57:25,158
Where do you go? What is her name?
Does she have a sister?

782
00:57:25,247 --> 00:57:27,317
Good night, Streebek.

783
00:57:29,967 --> 00:57:33,039
Truth is, l don't care where you go.

784
00:57:36,927 --> 00:57:38,963
Yeah, l do.
l gotta know.

785
00:58:05,407 --> 00:58:07,238
l knew it.

786
00:58:07,327 --> 00:58:09,716
lt's Nightmare on Elm Street.

787
00:58:09,807 --> 00:58:13,322
- That would make him Freddie Krueger.
- [ Coyote Howling ]

788
00:58:14,647 --> 00:58:17,036
We're gonna be driving along some night
and the lighting's gonna be bad.

789
00:58:17,127 --> 00:58:21,086
He's gonna mistake me for some
pretty coed, and out comes that claw.

790
00:58:21,167 --> 00:58:25,285
[ Snarling, Screaming ]

791
00:58:26,327 --> 00:58:28,283
170 pounds of ground chuck.

792
00:58:30,847 --> 00:58:35,716
Who knows what kind of thrill-seeking
hose monster he's got stashed in there?

793
00:58:42,207 --> 00:58:45,643
My God, he's dating Mother Goose!
Hey, Joe!

794
00:58:45,727 --> 00:58:48,844
Streebek, what are you doing here?

795
00:58:48,927 --> 00:58:52,158
- Who is this nice-looking young man?
- He's nobody.

796
00:58:52,247 --> 00:58:53,965
My partner.

797
00:58:54,047 --> 00:58:57,005
Streebek, introduce yourself
to my grandmother, quickly.

798
00:58:57,087 --> 00:59:00,523
Well, what a pleasant surprise.

799
00:59:00,607 --> 00:59:02,438
Granny Friday.

800
00:59:02,527 --> 00:59:05,883
She's my maternal grandmother.
Her name is Mundy.

801
00:59:07,127 --> 00:59:10,278
Why don't we discuss this over dinner?
lt's my birthday.

802
00:59:10,367 --> 00:59:14,440
We're going to the Brown Derby.
Do join us, Detective Swayback.

803
00:59:14,527 --> 00:59:16,358
- Streebek.
- Pep.

804
00:59:16,447 --> 00:59:18,358
l don't think it's a good idea.

805
00:59:19,087 --> 00:59:21,806
- Why not, Joe?
- Yeah, Joe, why not?

806
00:59:21,887 --> 00:59:27,007
l've invited someone already
to join us, and you don't know her.

807
00:59:27,087 --> 00:59:28,361
- Her?
- Her?

808
00:59:28,447 --> 00:59:31,519
Joe! You have a date?

809
00:59:36,407 --> 00:59:38,875
l'm so proud!

810
00:59:42,167 --> 00:59:45,477
Well, it looks like
l have a date, too.

811
00:59:45,567 --> 00:59:48,559
Granny Mundy, may l escort you
to Joe's car?

812
00:59:48,647 --> 00:59:52,003
l'd be privileged,
Detective Startrek.

813
00:59:55,927 --> 00:59:59,886
9:00 p.m. Exactly one night after
witnessing the satanic cult rally...

814
00:59:59,967 --> 01:00:04,279
l escorted my grandmother to her
favourite restaurant, the Brown Derby.

815
01:00:04,367 --> 01:00:08,997
There was someone l wanted her to meet,
and it wasn't Detective Streebek.

816
01:00:09,087 --> 01:00:11,396
Sergeant Friday, your table is ready.

817
01:00:11,487 --> 01:00:14,206
l took the liberty of pouring
the Dom Perignon.

818
01:00:14,287 --> 01:00:15,686
What Dom Perignon?

819
01:00:15,767 --> 01:00:19,840
l stopped and phoned in an order
in honour of Granny Mundy's birthday.

820
01:00:19,927 --> 01:00:22,839
You'd want her to have
the most expensive kind, wouldn't you?

821
01:00:22,927 --> 01:00:26,761
What a thoughtful gesture!
Don't you think so, Joe?

822
01:00:26,847 --> 01:00:30,044
Yes, Granny.
lt was very considerate of him.

823
01:00:38,887 --> 01:00:42,118
Hello, Joe.
Guess l'm early.

824
01:00:42,207 --> 01:00:44,038
l was kind of excited.

825
01:00:44,127 --> 01:00:46,118
You sly minx!

826
01:00:47,767 --> 01:00:50,486
l'd like you to meet my maternal
grandmother, Mrs. Grace Mundy.

827
01:00:50,567 --> 01:00:52,478
Granny, this is
the virgin Connie Swail.

828
01:00:54,367 --> 01:00:55,720
You're kidding?

829
01:00:55,807 --> 01:00:57,638
Hi.

830
01:00:57,727 --> 01:01:01,276
Well, allow me.
The place of honour for Granny.

831
01:01:01,367 --> 01:01:03,597
- Thank you.
- Certainly.

832
01:01:06,047 --> 01:01:08,607
And if l may, a toast.

833
01:01:08,687 --> 01:01:10,086
To Granny Mundy.

834
01:01:10,167 --> 01:01:13,239
May you live as long as you want
but never want as long as you live.

835
01:01:15,167 --> 01:01:16,566
Hear! Hear!

836
01:01:19,807 --> 01:01:22,275
Ahhh.

837
01:01:22,367 --> 01:01:24,517
This is such a happy restaurant.

838
01:01:24,607 --> 01:01:27,485
Commissioner Kirkpatrick,
how nice to see you again.

839
01:01:27,567 --> 01:01:29,956
Reverend Whirley,
it's a privilege.

840
01:01:32,047 --> 01:01:33,878
An aperitif, perhaps?

841
01:01:33,967 --> 01:01:37,164
l once saw Alan Hale, Jr. in here.

842
01:01:37,247 --> 01:01:40,637
Alan Hale, Jr.! Wow!
''Gilligan, little buddy!''

843
01:01:40,727 --> 01:01:45,323
Don't order anything more expensive than
the Cobb salad. That is an order.

844
01:01:45,407 --> 01:01:48,046
Oh, my God!

845
01:01:48,127 --> 01:01:50,436
- Connie?
- That's him.

846
01:01:50,527 --> 01:01:52,597
That man with the collar.

847
01:01:52,687 --> 01:01:54,518
The Reverend Whirley?

848
01:01:54,607 --> 01:01:57,963
He's the one who kidnapped me
and threw me in that pit...

849
01:01:58,047 --> 01:02:00,117
with that horrible snake.

850
01:02:01,207 --> 01:02:04,040
l'll never forget his face
as long as l live.

851
01:02:04,127 --> 01:02:06,641
You have to be sure about this.

852
01:02:06,727 --> 01:02:09,480
How about very, very sure?

853
01:02:09,567 --> 01:02:11,842
l'm positive, Joe.

854
01:02:11,927 --> 01:02:13,724
That's him.

855
01:02:13,807 --> 01:02:15,684
The face behind the mask.

856
01:02:17,247 --> 01:02:19,715
The man who tried to kill me.

857
01:02:22,967 --> 01:02:25,879
Would you testify to that under oath
in a court of law?

858
01:02:25,967 --> 01:02:28,606
Wait a minute. Settle down.

859
01:02:28,687 --> 01:02:31,838
Let's think about this.
That is Jonathan Whirley.

860
01:02:31,927 --> 01:02:35,078
Head of the Moral Advance Movement
of America. He's a public hero.

861
01:02:35,167 --> 01:02:38,842
- You can't just walk up to him--
- Streebek.

862
01:02:38,927 --> 01:02:40,997
Vermin aren't allowed
inside restaurants.

863
01:02:41,087 --> 01:02:43,157
l'll be enforcing
the public health code.

864
01:02:44,927 --> 01:02:46,997
lf you'll both excuse me...

865
01:02:47,087 --> 01:02:50,443
l'm afraid
the second-highest duty calls.

866
01:02:55,487 --> 01:02:58,877
Joe, he is sitting with the commissioner
and our captain.

867
01:02:58,967 --> 01:03:02,277
Bust him now, tomorrow you'll
be mucking out stalls at Horse Patrol.

868
01:03:09,327 --> 01:03:10,680
Thank you.

869
01:03:12,647 --> 01:03:14,000
l am sorry.

870
01:03:14,087 --> 01:03:16,920
Hold it there, Whirley. Police Officer.
You're under arrest.

871
01:03:17,007 --> 01:03:19,316
l beg your pardon?
ls this some sort of feeble joke?

872
01:03:19,407 --> 01:03:24,845
Oh, it's a knee-slapper, if you consider
Penal Codes 484207 A597 and 217...

873
01:03:24,927 --> 01:03:27,600
theft, kidnapping, cruelty to animals,
attempted murder things to laugh about.

874
01:03:27,727 --> 01:03:30,082
l don't know
what you're talking about.

875
01:03:30,167 --> 01:03:32,840
My partner and l witnessed
that torchlight picnic you threw.

876
01:03:32,927 --> 01:03:36,442
We're gonna put you where your kind
always ends up: in a 7-by-7 cage...

877
01:03:36,527 --> 01:03:40,679
in some hundred-year-old penitentiary
with a wooden plank for a bed.

878
01:03:40,767 --> 01:03:44,077
Sure, this city isn't perfect. We need
a smut-free life for all our citizens.

879
01:03:44,167 --> 01:03:46,362
Cleaner streets, better schools,
a good hockey team.

880
01:03:46,447 --> 01:03:50,281
But the difference between you and me is
you made the promise, l'm gonna keep it.

881
01:04:03,687 --> 01:04:07,441
Our good reverend's an amazing
piece of work, isn't he, Jane?

882
01:04:07,527 --> 01:04:10,485
- May l call you Jane?
- No.

883
01:04:18,087 --> 01:04:20,237
Captain, Commissioner...

884
01:04:20,327 --> 01:04:23,239
l demand an immediate explanation
for this outrageous behaviour.

885
01:04:23,327 --> 01:04:25,363
lt's him again.

886
01:04:25,447 --> 01:04:27,756
Are you insane?

887
01:04:27,847 --> 01:04:31,442
Reverend Whirley abducted that girl,
had his men throw her in a pit...

888
01:04:31,527 --> 01:04:34,280
filled with polluted water
and a giant Bolivian jungle snake.

889
01:04:34,367 --> 01:04:36,927
These accusations are preposterous!

890
01:04:37,007 --> 01:04:40,636
l beg to differ. Ask him if he remembers
3,000 gallons of stolen...

891
01:04:40,727 --> 01:04:43,605
trichlornitromethane and the
pseudo-halogenic compound cyanogen...

892
01:04:43,687 --> 01:04:45,723
which, when mixed properly,
form a liquid fertilizer that burns...

893
01:04:45,807 --> 01:04:49,197
the throat, eyes, lungs, and nose,
and could cause vomiting and death.

894
01:04:49,287 --> 01:04:51,926
We're just about to eat here!

895
01:04:52,007 --> 01:04:55,682
Reverend Whirley, please accept
our most sincere apologies.

896
01:04:55,767 --> 01:04:58,804
Sergeant, you will remove
those handcuffs immediately.

897
01:04:58,887 --> 01:05:01,640
Then you will hand in your badge.
You are relieved from duty.

898
01:05:01,727 --> 01:05:03,206
But-- But--
But, Commissioner--

899
01:05:03,287 --> 01:05:04,720
Now!

900
01:05:06,647 --> 01:05:08,683
Yes, sir. Ma'am.

901
01:05:08,767 --> 01:05:11,884
l don't care.
l'm absolutely humiliated.

902
01:05:11,967 --> 01:05:15,846
l know the young man was overzealous,
but he springs from a great tradition.

903
01:05:15,927 --> 01:05:19,078
Commissioner, won't you please
change your mind?

904
01:05:30,567 --> 01:05:34,003
l'm afraid l'll have to take
your badge and gun.

905
01:05:34,087 --> 01:05:37,966
- lf we could just please--
- l don't want to discuss it!

906
01:05:38,047 --> 01:05:40,561
Just hand them over.

907
01:06:09,407 --> 01:06:14,242
Look, Joe, don't worry. l'm still
on active duty. l'm building a case.

908
01:06:14,327 --> 01:06:16,522
You're building nothin'.

909
01:06:16,607 --> 01:06:20,600
lf l ever hear you've come
within one mile of Reverend Whirley...

910
01:06:20,687 --> 01:06:22,598
l'll have your badge for breakfast!

911
01:06:22,687 --> 01:06:25,679
- Understood?
- Yes, sir.

912
01:06:33,447 --> 01:06:37,360
lt was very nice of you to try
and take us out to dinner, Joe.

913
01:06:37,447 --> 01:06:41,042
Yeah. Thanks, Joe, for everything.

914
01:06:42,727 --> 01:06:47,437
Let's not stand around here moping.
l'm hungry! Let's go for chili dogs.

915
01:06:47,527 --> 01:06:52,647
Granny, have you ever eaten a chili dog
off the back of a motorcycle?

916
01:06:52,727 --> 01:06:54,558
Not till now.

917
01:06:54,647 --> 01:06:57,957
You smooth-talking son of a gun.

918
01:07:07,607 --> 01:07:10,405
- Thank you.
- You're welcome.

919
01:07:15,287 --> 01:07:17,960
l'm very sorry
you lost your job, Joe.

920
01:07:18,047 --> 01:07:20,242
l really did have
a very good time.

921
01:07:20,327 --> 01:07:22,443
l'm glad, Connie.

922
01:07:22,527 --> 01:07:25,439
Now, fasten your seat belt.
l can still effect a citizen's arrest.

923
01:07:25,527 --> 01:07:28,724
l don't want to ruin a wonderful evening
by bringing you in on a misdemeanour.

924
01:07:30,007 --> 01:07:31,759
That was a joke.

925
01:07:32,847 --> 01:07:35,077
Oh.

926
01:07:49,167 --> 01:07:51,283
Oh, Joe!

927
01:07:51,367 --> 01:07:53,278
Look at the stars!

928
01:07:53,367 --> 01:07:55,437
Dozens of them.

929
01:07:57,727 --> 01:08:01,766
You know, when l was a little girl...

930
01:08:01,847 --> 01:08:04,680
l used to wish upon
a different star every night...

931
01:08:04,767 --> 01:08:08,043
for that special someone to come along.

932
01:08:08,127 --> 01:08:10,641
Someone with whom
l could share...

933
01:08:12,647 --> 01:08:14,638
everything.

934
01:08:19,007 --> 01:08:21,316
l guess that's not so unusual.

935
01:08:22,207 --> 01:08:25,643
All girls do that, don't they, Joe?

936
01:08:25,727 --> 01:08:28,241
Some guys do, too, Connie.

937
01:08:31,887 --> 01:08:34,162
- Joe?
- That's me.

938
01:08:35,687 --> 01:08:37,518
Was there ever...

939
01:08:40,167 --> 01:08:41,520
anyone else?

940
01:08:41,607 --> 01:08:43,359
Of course there was.

941
01:08:44,567 --> 01:08:46,319
Oh.

942
01:08:46,407 --> 01:08:50,082
Actually, l've only been driving
with Streebek a couple of days.

943
01:08:50,167 --> 01:08:53,284
- Before that l was with Frank.
- That's not what l meant.

944
01:09:13,687 --> 01:09:17,839
- [ Banging ]
- [ Screaming ]

945
01:09:17,927 --> 01:09:20,646
Goodness! Earthquake! lt's the big one!

946
01:09:20,727 --> 01:09:22,957
Joe, help!

947
01:09:23,047 --> 01:09:24,605
Request Code 3.
Officer in distress.

948
01:09:24,687 --> 01:09:27,360
Assist officer.
l'll handle this. Calm down.

949
01:09:29,367 --> 01:09:32,996
