Look, there's the mayor.

1052
01:17:45,567 --> 01:17:48,320
Pretty clever of Whirley manoeuvring
him up here to Caesar's party.

1053
01:17:48,407 --> 01:17:50,557
He's got both people
he wants to eliminate in one place.

1054
01:17:50,647 --> 01:17:53,957
Hey, isn't that Whirley's car?

1055
01:17:54,047 --> 01:17:56,356
Good evening, Reverend.

1056
01:17:56,447 --> 01:17:58,244
Child.

1057
01:17:58,327 --> 01:18:00,602
l don't see Connie.

1058
01:18:00,687 --> 01:18:04,885
- The next car comes, follow me in.
- Wait. You can't go in there.

1059
01:18:04,967 --> 01:18:08,243
- When did you become Miss Manners?
- First, you don't have a warrant.

1060
01:18:08,327 --> 01:18:11,603
Penal Code 836: A police officer
may make an arrest without a warrant...

1061
01:18:11,687 --> 01:18:13,518
if he believes there's probable cause--

1062
01:18:13,607 --> 01:18:16,360
You're not a police officer any more.

1063
01:18:19,207 --> 01:18:21,846
l hate to be the one to break
that to you, but it's the truth.

1064
01:18:21,927 --> 01:18:24,725
You charge in there now,
you'll never get your badge back.

1065
01:18:24,807 --> 01:18:26,718
Whirley's the only one
that knows where Connie is.

1066
01:18:26,807 --> 01:18:29,002
He'll tell or l'll shove that collar
so far down his throat...

1067
01:18:29,087 --> 01:18:30,918
l'll have to take off his shoes
to wring his neck.

1068
01:18:31,007 --> 01:18:34,841
You're not thinking like a cop any more.
You're thinking like a man in love.

1069
01:18:34,927 --> 01:18:37,441
Watch your language, mister!

1070
01:18:38,367 --> 01:18:40,517
Oh, Joe, l--

1071
01:18:40,607 --> 01:18:43,565
You've never had these feelings before,
have you?

1072
01:18:45,127 --> 01:18:46,958
Almost.

1073
01:18:47,047 --> 01:18:49,197
l had a kitten once.

1074
01:18:49,287 --> 01:18:52,723
This is gonna be a little different.
Connie won't be sleeping in a box...

1075
01:18:52,807 --> 01:18:56,516
or meowing all night
or climbing up your drapes.

1076
01:18:56,607 --> 01:19:01,044
Or maybe she will. You both are sort of
starting from scratch with this thing.

1077
01:19:01,127 --> 01:19:02,640
Get out of my way!

1078
01:19:02,727 --> 01:19:07,039
Last time you went after Whirley, you
got suspended. Now you'll get arrested.

1079
01:19:07,127 --> 01:19:12,042
- On what charge, Junior?
- How about Section 146-A?

1080
01:19:13,247 --> 01:19:16,842
That's right.
lmpersonating a police officer.

1081
01:19:18,247 --> 01:19:21,045
lt's for your own good, Joe.

1082
01:19:21,127 --> 01:19:23,687
ln spite of every logical instinct
l've ever had...

1083
01:19:23,767 --> 01:19:26,565
l consider you a real friend.

1084
01:19:29,927 --> 01:19:32,236
- Wait.
- Joe, go home.

1085
01:19:32,327 --> 01:19:34,238
There's nothing more you can do here.
Believe me.

1086
01:19:34,327 --> 01:19:37,125
By the way, my name is Pep.

1087
01:19:38,407 --> 01:19:42,002
lt's not mister, junior,
bub or Streebek. lt's Pep.

1088
01:19:44,007 --> 01:19:47,556
Friendships start with first names...

1089
01:19:47,647 --> 01:19:49,000
Joe.

1090
01:20:11,207 --> 01:20:13,516
[ Jerry Caesar ]
Thank you so much for comin'.

1091
01:20:13,607 --> 01:20:16,041
Your Honour, pleased you could make it.

1092
01:20:16,127 --> 01:20:17,685
You, too, Reverend.

1093
01:20:17,767 --> 01:20:21,282
Let's just drop the fake civility.
Okay, Caesar?

1094
01:20:21,367 --> 01:20:24,996
- You have a cheque for the Reverend.
- l do, all in due time.

1095
01:20:26,127 --> 01:20:29,164
lf it would make us all feel better...

1096
01:20:29,247 --> 01:20:31,886
why don't l hold on to it
until the formal presentation?

1097
01:20:33,487 --> 01:20:35,318
Well, whatever.

1098
01:20:42,367 --> 01:20:45,677
You're just in time. We're about
to start our cultural talent show.

1099
01:20:45,767 --> 01:20:47,598
Why don't you pull up a pew next to me?

1100
01:20:47,687 --> 01:20:51,475
Reverend, l'm sure you'll find
these gals socially redeemin'.

